11:39.032 --> 11:40.408
A SHARK?

11:40.534 --> 11:43.244
[ RADAR BEEPING ]

11:43.370 --> 11:45.121
THE BIGGEST FISH MY PULSER

11:45.246 --> 11:47.790
DETECTS IS A SOMEWHAT PUDGY COD.

11:47.915 --> 11:48.791
[ SCREAMING CONTINUES ]

11:48.916 --> 11:50.627
>> FOR THE LOVE OF MY APPROVAL

11:50.751 --> 11:52.420
RATINGS, FIND OUT WHERE THAT

11:52.546 --> 11:53.547
SHARK CAME FROM!

11:53.672 --> 11:54.297
[ CELLPHONE BEEPS ]

11:54.422 --> 11:54.964
[ KEYBOARD CLACKS ]

11:55.089 --> 11:56.466
[ RADAR BEEPING ]

11:56.591 --> 11:58.926
SOMETHING'S JAMMING MY SIGNAL.

11:59.052 --> 11:59.844
[ CRASH ]

11:59.969 --> 12:01.638
WHAT IN NEWTON'S APPLE IS --

12:01.762 --> 12:02.430
[ CRASH ]

12:02.556 --> 12:03.598
AAH!

12:03.722 --> 12:07.602
[ GASPS ]

12:07.726 --> 12:09.103
[ RADAR BEEPING ]

12:09.229 --> 12:14.442
>> HMM.

12:14.568 --> 12:15.776
AGAIN?

12:15.902 --> 12:17.612
WELL, THIS TIME I HOPE YOU

12:17.736 --> 12:19.698
SMILED FOR THE CAMERA.

12:27.247 --> 12:27.955
[ GASPS ]

12:28.081 --> 12:30.958
[ HORN HONKS ]

12:31.084 --> 12:32.293
CHIEF!

12:32.419 --> 12:35.463
YOU'LL WANT TO SEE THIS.

12:35.589 --> 12:37.798
[ KEYBOARD CLACKING ]

12:37.924 --> 12:38.799
[ ComTab BEEPS ]

12:38.925 --> 12:40.051
>> NOT A REAL SHARK, MR. MAYOR,

12:40.176 --> 12:41.344
BUT BEST TO STAY OUT OF THE

12:41.469 --> 12:43.012
WATER FOR NOW.

12:43.137 --> 12:45.848
>> INCREDIBLE.

12:45.973 --> 12:47.183
[ COMPUTER BEEPS ]

12:47.308 --> 12:48.976
>> HEY, DOC, YOU THINK SOMEONE'S

12:49.102 --> 12:50.270
INSIDE THAT SUBMARINE?

12:50.395 --> 12:51.896
>> JAMMING SIGNALS, CHANGING

12:52.021 --> 12:53.398
COURSE TO ATTACK -- I WOULD

12:53.523 --> 12:54.357
THINK SO.

12:54.482 --> 12:55.774
>> I'LL CONTACT THE SUB ON THE

12:55.900 --> 12:57.485
EMERGENCY MARITIME CHANNEL, TRY

12:57.611 --> 12:59.820
TO GET TO THE BOTTOM OF THIS.

12:59.946 --> 13:01.531
>> WHOEVER'S DRIVING THAT THING

13:01.656 --> 13:03.283
MUST REALLY HATE YOUR TECH, DOC.

13:03.408 --> 13:04.951
I MEAN, FIRST IT ATTACKED YOUR

13:05.076 --> 13:06.661
PULSERS, THEN YOUR FISHING ROD.

13:06.785 --> 13:07.995
>> MY FISHING ROD?

13:08.121 --> 13:08.829
[ GASPS ]

13:08.955 --> 13:10.373
AH! ELECTROMAGNETICS!

13:10.498 --> 13:12.292
EVERYTHING THE SUBMARINE HAS

13:12.417 --> 13:13.710
TARGETED USES THEM.

13:13.834 --> 13:15.836
THE ELECTROMAGNETIC PULSES MUST

13:15.962 --> 13:17.297
BE WHAT ATTRACTS IT.

13:17.422 --> 13:19.299
BUT WHY IT WOULD WANT TO STOP

13:19.424 --> 13:20.841
THEM, I HAVE NO IDEA.

13:20.967 --> 13:22.176
>> NO ANSWER FROM THE SUB.

13:22.302 --> 13:23.762
IF WE WANT TO TALK TO THE PILOT,

13:23.886 --> 13:25.305
WE'LL HAVE TO CATCH HIM FIRST.

13:25.430 --> 13:26.973
>> UNFORTUNATELY MY SENSORS

13:27.098 --> 13:28.266
WON'T BE MUCH HELP.

13:28.391 --> 13:30.059
THAT SUB JAMS THEM, THEN RAMS

13:30.184 --> 13:31.018
THEM.

13:31.144 --> 13:32.520
>> FINDING THAT CRAFT BLIND WILL

13:32.646 --> 13:34.188
TAKE MONTHS.

13:34.314 --> 13:35.398
>> NO, IT WON'T.

13:35.523 --> 13:36.983
IT'S LIKE FISHING, DAD.

13:37.108 --> 13:38.943
YOU JUST HAVE TO USE THE RIGHT

13:39.068 --> 13:42.614
BAIT.

13:42.739 --> 13:44.115
[ TV CHATTER ]

13:44.240 --> 13:45.116
[ TV TURNS OFF ]

13:45.241 --> 13:46.951
>> CAN'T BELIEVE WE GOT TO DITCH

13:47.076 --> 13:48.495
THE FISHING TRIP THIS YEAR.

13:48.620 --> 13:49.870
GUESS WE OWE THE BOTS A

13:49.996 --> 13:50.871
THANK-YOU.

13:50.997 --> 13:52.373
>> YOU KNOW, SOME OF THOSE DAYS

13:52.499 --> 13:54.083
ON THE BOAT, THEY WERE KIND OF

13:54.208 --> 13:55.084
FUN.

13:55.209 --> 13:56.336
>> YEAH, REMEMBER THE TIME KADE

13:56.461 --> 13:58.045
ACCIDENTALLY ATE SOME OF DAD'S

13:58.171 --> 13:59.046
BAIT?

13:59.172 --> 14:00.047
>> [ Chuckling ] IT WASN'T BAD.

14:00.173 --> 14:01.549
OR, HEY, HOW ABOUT THE TIME YOU

14:01.675 --> 14:02.967
THOUGHT YOU'D CAUGHT THAT RARE

14:03.092 --> 14:03.926
FISH?

14:04.051 --> 14:04.843
>> OH, AND DAD DIDN'T HAVE THE

14:04.969 --> 14:06.387
HEART TO TELL YOU IT WAS A BOOT.

14:06.513 --> 14:09.724
[ LAUGHTER ]

14:09.848 --> 14:11.392
>> THINK IF WE MEET HIM AT THE

14:11.518 --> 14:13.144
DOCK IT'LL STILL COUNT AS FAMILY

14:13.269 --> 14:13.936
TIME?

14:14.061 --> 14:15.689
>> COULDN'T HURT TO TRY.

14:17.774 --> 14:20.652
[ PULSER CHIRPING ]

14:20.777 --> 14:22.195
>> I UPGRADED THE PULSER TO

14:22.320 --> 14:23.321
PRODUCE A LOW-RANGE

14:23.446 --> 14:24.614
ELECTROMAGNETIC BURST.

14:24.739 --> 14:26.157
>> THERE'S NO WAY THE SUB'S

14:26.282 --> 14:27.701
CAPTAIN IS GONNA BE ABLE TO

14:27.826 --> 14:29.076
RESIST THAT.

14:32.372 --> 14:34.415
>> WHOA, HOLD ON, CODY.

14:34.541 --> 14:37.251
THIS COULD BE DANGEROUS.

14:37.377 --> 14:39.295
I NEED YOU ON THE ComTab KEEPING

14:39.420 --> 14:40.505
AN EYE ON THINGS.

14:40.630 --> 14:42.215
>> I'LL DROP HIM OFF AT THE

14:42.340 --> 14:43.675
PIER.

14:43.800 --> 14:45.510
>> I'VE HAD IT WITH WAITING FOR

14:45.635 --> 14:46.845
THINGS TO COME TO US.

14:46.969 --> 14:48.638
>> ISN'T THAT THE DEFINITION OF

14:48.763 --> 14:49.389
FISHING?

14:49.514 --> 14:52.141
[ PULSER CHIRPING ]

14:52.266 --> 14:53.976
>> CHIEF, A WORD.

14:54.101 --> 14:55.770
ONCE WE LOCATE THE ROGUE VESSEL,

14:55.895 --> 14:57.522
HOW DO YOU INTEND TO APPREHEND

14:57.647 --> 14:58.439
IT?

14:58.565 --> 14:59.440
>> WE LEAD THE SUB TO THAT

14:59.566 --> 15:00.941
COVE.

15:01.067 --> 15:03.110
ONCE IT'S INSIDE, WE BLOCK THE

15:03.236 --> 15:03.944
WAY OUT.

15:04.070 --> 15:05.988
>> CAPTAIN! AHOY!

15:06.113 --> 15:09.992
[ CHIRPING CONTINUES ]

15:10.117 --> 15:11.285
>> LET'S SEE IF IT TAKES THE

15:11.411 --> 15:11.911
BAIT.

15:12.036 --> 15:12.912
[ MOTOR REVS ]

15:18.793 --> 15:21.504
>> [ GASPS ]

15:21.629 --> 15:23.423
CHIEF, THE SUBMARINE HAS

15:23.548 --> 15:25.341
DEVIATED FROM ITS COURSE.

15:25.466 --> 15:30.179
[ ENGINE SLOWS ]

15:30.304 --> 15:32.181
[ CHIRPING CONTINUES ]

15:32.306 --> 15:33.600
>> WHY WOULD THE SUBMARINE

15:33.725 --> 15:34.559
TARGET THE FERRY?

15:34.684 --> 15:36.185
>> THE SUB JUST FOUND SOMETHING

15:36.310 --> 15:37.144
BETTER.

15:37.270 --> 15:38.187
>> DON'T TELL ME -- THE FERRY

15:38.312 --> 15:39.439
USES ELECTROMAGNETICS?

15:39.564 --> 15:40.815
>> IN ITS STEERING MODULE,

15:40.940 --> 15:42.149
LOCATED DEEP IN THE HULL.

15:42.275 --> 15:43.651
>> BUT IF THE SUBMARINE RAMS

15:43.777 --> 15:45.069
THROUGH THAT SHIP'S HULL --

15:45.194 --> 15:46.654
>> SHE'LL BE GOING STRAIGHT TO

15:46.780 --> 15:49.156
DAVY JONES' LOCKER!

15:49.282 --> 15:50.991
I-IT'S BAD.

15:51.117 --> 15:53.202
[ CHIRPING CONTINUES ]

15:55.580 --> 15:57.457
[ PULSER CHIRPING ]

15:57.582 --> 15:58.416
>> [ GASPS ]

15:58.541 --> 16:00.251
CHIEF BURNS TO GRIFFIN ROCK

16:00.376 --> 16:01.043
FERRY.

16:01.168 --> 16:02.420
PREPARE FOR COLLISION.

16:02.545 --> 16:03.963
Captain Shaw, I repeat,

16:04.088 --> 16:04.798
incoming.

16:04.923 --> 16:06.966
Suggest evasive maneuvers.

16:07.091 --> 16:08.968
[ CHIRPING CONTINUES ]

16:09.093 --> 16:09.803
[ CRANK! ]

16:09.928 --> 16:10.428
>> DANG!

16:10.553 --> 16:11.679
>> All: [ GASP ]

16:21.731 --> 16:23.316
>> SUB'S TOO FAST FOR THE FERRY

16:23.441 --> 16:24.358
TO OUTRUN.

16:24.484 --> 16:25.693
WE'LL  HAVE TO GET THOSE FOLKS

16:25.819 --> 16:26.193
OFF.

16:26.319 --> 16:26.945
BLADES?

16:27.069 --> 16:29.071
>> AYE-AYE, CAPTAIN!

16:31.783 --> 16:33.200
>>  ISN'T THERE SOME WAY WE CAN

16:33.326 --> 16:34.368
STOP THAT SUBMARINE?

16:34.494 --> 16:35.954
>> PEOPLE COME FIRST, HEATWAVE.

16:36.078 --> 16:37.872
REMEMBER -- PATIENCE.

16:41.668 --> 16:43.336
>> HEATWAVE, WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

16:43.461 --> 16:44.838
>> I'M ALL OUT OF PATIENCE.

16:44.963 --> 16:46.589
IF THAT SUB WON'T COME TO US --

16:46.714 --> 16:48.257
>> HEATWAVE, IF YOU RECALL OUR

16:48.382 --> 16:50.050
DENSITY RENDERED US INCAPABLE OF

16:50.176 --> 16:50.969
BUOYANCY.

16:51.093 --> 16:52.219
>> I DON'T INTEND TO FLOAT.

16:52.345 --> 16:54.472
I INTEND TO  DRIVE.

17:02.981 --> 17:05.024
>> RESCUE BOTS, ROLL TO THE

17:05.149 --> 17:10.196
RESCUE!

17:10.321 --> 17:12.573
[ ENGINES REV ]

17:15.576 --> 17:20.289
[ PULSER CHIRPING ]

17:20.414 --> 17:21.290
>> All: [ SCREAM ]

17:21.415 --> 17:22.959
>> GET TO THE LIFEBOAT!

17:40.018 --> 17:41.060
[ CHIRPING CONTINUES ]

17:41.185 --> 17:43.103
>> DAD, I'M BACK AT THE PIER.

17:47.525 --> 17:49.068
THE SUB'S HEADED FOR THE FERRY.

17:49.193 --> 17:50.737
>> AGAIN?

17:50.862 --> 17:54.073
THEN WE'RE OUT OF TIME.

17:54.198 --> 17:55.449
>> I DON'T THINK YOUR SHIP CAN

17:55.575 --> 17:56.617
TAKE ANOTHER HIT, ARTHUR.

17:56.743 --> 17:59.119
>> SAVE MY PASSENGERS.

17:59.245 --> 18:01.455
BUT THE CAPTAIN ALWAYS GOES DOWN

18:01.581 --> 18:02.749
WITH THIS SHIP!

18:02.874 --> 18:04.751
>> JUST THIS ONCE, DO ME A FAVOR

18:04.876 --> 18:06.794
AND GO  UP  WITH YOUR SHIP.

18:26.814 --> 18:29.859
>> [ GRUNTS ]

18:29.984 --> 18:30.818
>> [ GRUNTS ]

18:30.944 --> 18:32.028
[ MOTOR WHIRRING ]

18:32.152 --> 18:34.405
[ WHIRRING STOPS ]

18:39.410 --> 18:41.704
[ WHIRRING CONTINUES ]

18:44.665 --> 18:48.377
[ GRUNTING ]

18:48.502 --> 18:49.963
[ MOTOR STOPS ]

18:57.804 --> 18:58.846
>> [ GASPS ]

18:58.972 --> 19:02.182
TIME FOR THAT SWIM LESSON, GUYS!

19:02.308 --> 19:03.768
HOLD ON TIGHT, POINT YOURSELF

19:03.893 --> 19:05.436
TOWARD THE DOCK, AND KICK YOUR

19:05.561 --> 19:08.982
LEGS -- HARD!

19:09.107 --> 19:12.026
>> HMM. NOW,  THIS  IS A SPORT.

19:15.613 --> 19:16.363
>> OH, COME ON.

19:16.489 --> 19:17.531
I  NEVER  FELL OVERBOARD.

19:17.657 --> 19:18.783
>>  I  SAVED YOU, REMEMBER.

19:18.908 --> 19:20.367
>> [ Chuckling ] NO, YOU DIDN'T.

19:20.493 --> 19:21.077
>> I SO  DID.

19:21.201 --> 19:21.828
>> [ LAUGHS ]

19:21.953 --> 19:22.453
WHATEVER.

19:22.578 --> 19:23.329
>> [ GASPS ]

19:23.454 --> 19:24.497
REMEMBER THE TIME THE BOTS

19:24.622 --> 19:25.999
CAUGHT THE BIGGEST SHARK KNOWN

19:26.124 --> 19:32.171
TO MAN?

19:32.296 --> 19:33.464
>> LOOKS LIKE WE MISSED ONE OF

19:33.589 --> 19:34.674
THE MORE INTERESTING FISHING

19:34.799 --> 19:36.009
TRIPS.

19:36.134 --> 19:37.593
>> TO THE PILOT OF THIS

19:37.718 --> 19:39.637
SUBMARINE, THIS IS CHIEF BURNS

19:39.762 --> 19:41.472
OF THE GRIFFIN ROCK POLICE.

19:41.597 --> 19:43.223
COME OUT WITH YOUR HANDS UP.

19:49.147 --> 19:51.190
[ SIGHS ]

19:51.315 --> 19:53.026
WE HAVE YOU SURROUNDED.

19:53.151 --> 19:55.361
DO YOU UNDERSTAND?

19:58.072 --> 19:59.615
[ CLANG! HISS! ]

19:59.740 --> 20:00.783
>>  HATCH BREACH.

20:00.908 --> 20:02.409
SELF-DESTRUCT ACTIVATED.

20:02.535 --> 20:03.536
[ SIREN WAILS ]

20:03.661 --> 20:05.038
>> [ GASPS ]

20:05.163 --> 20:06.539
>> DAD, YOU NEED ANYTHING?

20:06.664 --> 20:07.581
>> [ GRUNTS ]

20:07.707 --> 20:08.541
YES!

20:08.666 --> 20:10.043
I NEED YOU TO GET OUT OF HERE!

20:10.168 --> 20:10.918
>> WOW.

20:11.044 --> 20:12.461
I THOUGHT HE MIGHT BE MAD,

20:12.586 --> 20:13.462
BUT --

20:13.587 --> 20:14.755
>> THE SUB IS GOING TO EXPLODE!

20:14.881 --> 20:17.591
GET EVERYONE TO SAFETY!

20:17.717 --> 20:19.635
>> ARGH! BELAY THAT!

20:19.760 --> 20:22.138
I'LL  PUT THIS RUST BUCKET

20:22.262 --> 20:24.473
20,000 LEAGUES UNDER THE SEA!

20:24.598 --> 20:25.725
>> BLADES, NO!

20:25.850 --> 20:27.309
IT'S TOO DANGEROUS!

20:27.434 --> 20:28.602
>> AYE, LASSIE.

20:28.728 --> 20:30.980
WISH ME FAIR WINDS.

20:35.860 --> 20:36.736
[ WAILING CONTINUES ]

20:36.861 --> 20:38.738
>>  SELF-DESTRUCT IN 3...

20:38.863 --> 20:39.488
>> AAH!

20:39.613 --> 20:41.741
IT WON'T COME LOOSE!

20:41.866 --> 20:42.616
>>  ...2...

20:42.742 --> 20:43.701
>> [ GRUNTS ]

20:43.826 --> 20:46.037
[ WAILING CONTINUES ]

20:46.162 --> 20:47.413
>>  ...1.

20:49.999 --> 20:50.457
>> [ GASPS ]

20:50.583 --> 20:50.958
>> OH, NO.

20:51.084 --> 20:52.668
>> DUDE.

20:59.299 --> 21:03.054
>> ARGH!

21:03.179 --> 21:04.889
>> YEAH, ALL RIGHT!

21:05.014 --> 21:06.182
>> WHOO-HOO!

21:06.306 --> 21:07.641
>> SO, WHO WAS DRIVING THAT

21:07.767 --> 21:08.392
THING, DAD?

21:08.517 --> 21:09.393
>> MUST HAVE BEEN

21:09.518 --> 21:12.230
SELF-PROPELLED.

21:12.354 --> 21:14.398
>> BUT SOMEBODY HAS TO BE BEHIND

21:14.523 --> 21:15.191
THIS.

21:15.315 --> 21:16.650
SOMEONE BUILT THE SUB AND

21:16.776 --> 21:18.277
PROGRAMMED IT TO ATTACK

21:18.402 --> 21:19.445
ELECTROMAGNETS.

21:19.570 --> 21:23.490
BUT WHO WOULD DO THAT AND WHY?

21:27.828 --> 21:29.622
HMM.
